SCOPE OF THE CONFERENCE AND THE EXHIBITION
   This Conference  will display  a range  of ongoing  projects, studies
and  initiatives  that  reflect  Russia's  needs  for  changes in higher
education, and  the application  of new  information, telecommunication,
and  distance  education  technologies  in  the  Russian educational and
training sectors.
   The  Conference  will  stimulate   the  investigation  of   practical
approaches in introducing Russians  into the new democratic  educational
system and  market-oriented economy  through distance  learning and mass
media,  as  well  as  to  providing  students and adults with world-wide
telecommunications access to higher education institutions and  training
agencies.
   The  goal  of  the  Exhibition  is to demonstrate modern information,
communication,   and   multimedia   technologies,   along   with   their
applications  in  education  and  training.   It will provide Conference
participants with  information on  the state-of-the-art  in creating the
learning environment and classrooms of the 21st century.

PROCEEDINGS AND THE MASS MEDIA
   Only those  papers which  are presented  at the  Conference as well as
the main  materials of  the electronic  discussion will  be published in
the official ICDED'94 Proceedings.
   The ICDED'94 activities will be monitored by the Russian press and TV.

OFFICIAL LANGUAGE
  The official  language of  the Conference  is English,  which will  be
used  for   all  presentations   and  printed   material.   Simultaneous
translation will be provided only at the opening and closing  ceremonies
of the Conference.

TOPICS OF THE CONFERENCE
Distance Education:
   *  Theory
   *  Quality and Standards; Recognition and Academic Mobility
   *  Higher  Education;  Training and  Re-training;  K-12 Education
   *  Economics,  Management  and  Marketing  of  Distance Education
   *  Priorities and Strategies
Educational Environment:
   *  Information Technologies in the Classroom
   *  Electronic Tutors and Testing Systems
   *  Multimedia
   *  Audio- and Video-Conferencing
   *  Computer Mediated Communications
   *  Artificial Intelligence
   *  Innovative Solutions
   183  paper   abstracts  have   been  received   by  the    Conference
Secretariat.  The  preliminary  Program   of  the  Conference  will   be
distributed in early May 1994.

BEST PAPER AWARDS
    Special  awards  will  be  made  to  the most original and practical
ideas for  implementing distance  education in  the Russian  context and
fostering  the  integration  of   Russian  higher  education  into   the
international system.   Those prizes  will be  remitted at  the  closing
ceremony of the ICDED'94.

GLOBAL LECTURE HALL (GLH (TM))
    On July  7, 1994  a multipoint-to-multipoint  multimedia interactive
video  conference  to  "COMPARE  AND  EVALUATE  AVAILABLE  TECHNOLOGIES:
LEARNING THROUGH USING" is planned. The objectives of the GLH:

  * To demonstrate  "Global Lecture  Hall" video  conference technology
    for the Moscow conference attendees,  so that they can compare  and
    evaluate various delivery technologies for their global  electronic
    distance education exchange across the Atlantic Ocean;

  * To  hold  "get-acquainted   face-to-face"  meeting  via   satellite
    between  American  and  Bulgarian  schools,  for  the University of
    Tennessee's   newly   launched   distance   education   program  on
    "Management  for  Sustainable  Natural  Resource  Development   and
    Environmental Protection";

  * To  demonstrate   cooperation  of   international  and    domestic,
    governmental,  industrial  and  academic  organizations  for global
    scale projects.

    If  you  are  interested  in  participating  in  this  event, please
contact the GLH  Moderator to obtain  a registration form.   Registrants
will then receive instructions for participation.

PLACE
    The Conference and the Exhibition will be held in the Main  Building
(Presidium)  of  the  Russian  Academy  of  Sciences (Leninsky prospect,
32a). It is situated  close to the center  of Moscow on Gagarin  square.
It  is  well  served  by  public  transportion  and  the subway (station
"Leninsky Prospect").

