TRAVEL
    Finnair  has  become  participating  air  carrier  for  the ICDED'94
Conference in Moscow. Finnair has established a very attractive  package
of  special  low  fares  and  excellent  connections  during  the period
preceding and  following the  Conference. Departures  are available from
major cities  in North  America, Europe,  and other  parts of the world,
and arrangements  can be  made to  support attendance  at other meetings
and conferences in  the region in  the same time  period. Information on
flights and  other trip-related  arrangements for  ICDED'94 participants
can be obtained through the Conference Travel Agency.
    On the 4th  and 8th of  July 1994 special  buses will drive  between
the Sheremetievo 2  airport and the  hotels reserved for  the Conference
participants.  During the Conference you can easily order a car  through
the Conference Service Center  for individual transportation within  the
Moscow region.

APPLICATION FOR RUSSIAN VISA
    To obtain a Business Visa submit the following paperwork
to the Russian Consulate in your country:
  - Visa Application Form (please, request the Form from
the Russian Consulate);
  - a copy of pages of the passport with personal data;
  - three passport-size photographs;
  - your letter of invitation which you will receive upon registration
as a participant of the ICDED'94;
  - money order or company check payable to the Russian Embassy
(the fee depends on the processing period).
  Visa support  for the  ICDED'94 participants  will be  provided by the
State Committee for Higher Education of the Russian Federation.  Please,
carefully fill in the  Visa Information in the  Participant Registration
Form.

ACCOMMODATIONS
  We suggest the following hotels:

  President Hotel (1st class)
  ul. Dimitrova, 24 (metro station "Oktabrskaya")

